  "culture": {
    "title": "Greeting with warmth and respect",
    "text": "Spanish-speaking cultures often value warm greetings. A simple hola plus mucho gusto can make a first meeting feel respectful. In many family settings, greetings may include handshakes, hugs, or cheek kisses depending on closeness and region. When unsure, start politely with usted and follow the other person's tone."
  },
