    "title": "How native speakers really greet",
    "notes": [
      "Many speakers shorten buenas tardes or buenas noches to buenas.",
      "¿Qué tal? is a very common natural greeting, especially in Spain.",
      "In Mexico, ¿qué onda? is casual and friendly, but not formal.",
      "Native speakers often combine greetings: Hola, ¿qué tal? Mucho gusto.",
      "The response bien, gracias, ¿y tú? is simple, polite, and always useful."
    ]
  },
